01:15:59,774 --> 01:16:02,140
Angus?

796
01:16:32,974 --> 01:16:36,569
Stop, Angus!
Look!

797
01:16:36,611 --> 01:16:38,272
We could have run
the farm together,

798
01:16:38,313 --> 01:16:39,678
if you hadn't
ruined everything!

799
01:16:39,714 --> 01:16:41,375
If you hadn't tried
to kill me!

800
01:16:41,416 --> 01:16:43,543
Now it has to end.

801
01:17:58,727 --> 01:18:00,285
What?

802
01:18:18,646 --> 01:18:20,113
Come in.

803
01:18:21,983 --> 01:18:24,042
Speak up.

804
01:18:24,085 --> 01:18:26,781
Hold him, boy.

805
01:18:26,821 --> 01:18:28,686
Hold him.

806
01:18:28,723 --> 01:18:30,623
Hold him, boy.

807
01:18:32,694 --> 01:18:34,787
Get down.
Get down.

808
01:18:37,232 --> 01:18:39,632
Hold him.

809
01:18:45,573 --> 01:18:48,303
Hold him, boy.

810
01:19:10,298 --> 01:19:11,731
What?

811
01:19:37,458 --> 01:19:40,222
Tucker.
You're okay.

812
01:19:41,396 --> 01:19:42,886
Oh!

813
01:20:00,148 --> 01:20:01,581
What is that?

814
01:20:01,616 --> 01:20:04,346
Just a little something
I picked up in the lab.

815
01:20:04,385 --> 01:20:06,512
Should clear up your worms.
Fix your fly strike too.

816
01:20:24,606 --> 01:20:26,631
Anyway,
pull your finger out.

817
01:20:26,674 --> 01:20:28,642
We've got work to do.

818
01:20:32,847 --> 01:20:35,407
Hold 'em, Dice.
Hold 'em. Good dog.

819
01:20:43,324 --> 01:20:46,259
How much of
that stuff is there?

820
01:20:46,294 --> 01:20:48,387
Not enough for
all of them.

821
01:20:52,267 --> 01:20:54,497
Jeez!

822
01:20:58,806 --> 01:21:01,468
Angus, it's over.

823
01:21:01,509 --> 01:21:04,774
No, this is
just the beginning.

824
01:21:05,780 --> 01:21:07,008
Come back!

825
01:21:09,117 --> 01:21:10,675
My babies.

826
01:21:10,718 --> 01:21:13,653
Have me again.

827
01:21:49,157 --> 01:21:50,715
Methane.

828
01:21:58,700 --> 01:22:00,895
Get in behind!

829
01:22:26,728 --> 01:22:27,854
Last one.

830
01:22:27,895 --> 01:22:29,863
There's a nice bit of
wool on that, actually.

831
01:22:29,897 --> 01:22:32,798
- Reckon we should hang onto this one?
- He's a bit toey, but...

832
01:22:32,834 --> 01:22:34,131
Could make good eating.

833
01:22:41,442 --> 01:22:43,637
This is for you.

834
01:22:47,648 --> 01:22:49,741
What do you reckon, boss?

835
01:22:49,784 --> 01:22:51,979
Organic farming?

836
01:22:55,256 --> 01:22:57,520
Nothing but trouble,
this modern stuff.

837
01:22:57,558 --> 01:23:00,026
Better just to stick with the way
we've always done things, eh?

838
01:23:04,932 --> 01:23:08,333
I've eaten a rabbit.

839
01:23:11,506 --> 01:23:13,736
Blanket, dear?

840
01:23:13,775 --> 01:23:16,903
Let's see how
we go, eh?

841
01:23:23,051 --> 01:23:24,541
Snack?

842
01:23:24,585 --> 01:23:27,110
- What are they?
- Mountain oysters.

843
01:23:27,155 --> 01:23:29,555
Well, I do eat
a bit of seafood.

844
01:23:32,527 --> 01:23:34,427
No.

845
01:23:34,462 --> 01:23:36,430
Mm, it's good.

846
01:23:36,464 --> 01:23:38,762
Of course
it is, dear.

847
01:23:43,738 --> 01:23:46,605
You know you're eating
sheep's balls, don't you?

848
01:23:48,776 --> 01:23:50,243
Don't waste it.

849
01:23:54,182 --> 01:23:56,673
They'll grow on you.

850
01:23:58,719 --> 01:24:01,779
What is happening here?

851
01:24:01,823 --> 01:24:04,792
No seriously, you could
have an organic compost heap.

852
01:24:04,826 --> 01:24:06,726
Or a worm farm.
